Configure an SNMP agent and Community String in Windows 2012
1. Log into your dedicated server using Remote Desktop
2. Click on Windows Key > Administrative Tools > Server Manager.
3. Click Manage >  Add Roles and Features.
4. Click Next > Next > Next > Next. Verify SNMP Services are installed. Click Cancel. If SNMP is not installed, contact Support.  
￼

1. Click on Windows Key > Administrative Tools > Services.
2. Right click on SNMP Service and click on Properties.
3. Click on the Security tab. 
4. Type your randomized 8 - 10 character connection string. Be sure to make it Read Only, not Read Write.  
￼
5.   
6. Click on Add.
